msgid ""
"Tatra vata maṃ bhayaṃ vā sārajjaṃ vā okkamissatīti nimittametaṃ, sāriputta, "
"na samanupassāmi."
msgstr "But I don’t see any reason to feel afraid or insecure."

msgctxt "mn12:30.10"
msgid ""
"Etamahaṃ, sāriputta, nimittaṃ asamanupassanto khemappatto abhayappatto "
"vesārajjappatto viharāmi."
msgstr "Since I see no such reason, I live secure, fearless, and assured."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya31"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc31"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:31.1"
msgid "Yo kho maṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ jānantaṃ evaṃ passantaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When I know and see in this way, suppose someone were to say this:"

msgctxt "mn12:31.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi samaṇassa gotamassa uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso, "
"takkapariyāhataṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ "
"sayampaṭibhānan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has no superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision "
"worthy of the noble ones …’ "

msgctxt "mn12:31.3"
msgid ""
"taṃ, sāriputta, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ "
"appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""
"Unless they give up that speech and that thought, and let go of that view, "
"they will be cast down to hell."

msgctxt "mn12:31.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, sāriputta, vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:31.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā "
"yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya32"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc32"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:32.1"
msgid "Catasso kho imā, sāriputta, yoniyo."
msgstr "Sāriputta, there are these four kinds of reproduction."

msgctxt "mn12:32.2"
msgid "Katamā catasso?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "mn12:32.3"
msgid "Aṇḍajā yoni, jalābujā yoni, saṃsedajā yoni, opapātikā yoni."
msgstr ""
"Reproduction for creatures born from an egg, from a womb, from moisture, or "
"spontaneously."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya33"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:33.1"
msgid "Katamā ca, sāriputta, aṇḍajā yoni?"
msgstr "And what is reproduction from an egg?"

msgctxt "mn12:33.2"
msgid "Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā aṇḍakosaṃ abhinibbhijja jāyanti—"
msgstr "There are beings who are born by breaking out of an eggshell."

msgctxt "mn12:33.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, aṇḍajā yoni."
msgstr "This is called reproduction from an egg."

msgctxt "mn12:33.4"
msgid "Katamā ca, sāriputta, jalābujā yoni?"
msgstr "And what is reproduction from a womb?"

msgctxt "mn12:33.5"
msgid "Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā vatthikosaṃ abhinibbhijja jāyanti—"
msgstr "There are beings who are born by breaking out of the amniotic sac."

msgctxt "mn12:33.6"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, jalābujā yoni."
msgstr "This is called reproduction from a womb."

msgctxt "mn12:33.7"
msgid "Katamā ca, sāriputta, saṃsedajā yoni?"
msgstr "And what is reproduction from moisture?"

msgctxt "mn12:33.8"
msgid ""
"Ye kho te, sāriputta, sattā pūtimacche vā jāyanti pūtikuṇape vā pūtikummāse "
"vā candanikāye vā oḷigalle vā jāyanti—"
msgstr ""
"There are beings who are born in a rotten fish, in a rotten corpse, in "
"rotten dough, in a cesspool or a sump."

msgctxt "mn12:33.9"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, saṃsedajā yoni."
msgstr "This is called reproduction from moisture."

msgctxt "mn12:33.10"
msgid "Katamā ca, sāriputta, opapātikā yoni?"
msgstr "And what is spontaneous reproduction?"

msgctxt "mn12:33.11"
msgid "Devā, nerayikā, ekacce ca manussā, ekacce ca vinipātikā—"
msgstr ""
"Gods, hell-beings, certain humans, and certain beings in the lower realms."

msgctxt "mn12:33.12"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, sāriputta, opapātikā yoni."
msgstr "This is called spontaneous reproduction."

msgctxt "mn12:33.13"
msgid "Imā kho, sāriputta, catasso yoniyo."
msgstr "These are the four kinds of reproduction."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya34"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc33"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:34.1"
msgid "Yo kho maṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ jānantaṃ evaṃ passantaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When I know and see in this way, suppose someone were to say this:"

msgctxt "mn12:34.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi samaṇassa gotamassa uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso, "
"takkapariyāhataṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ "
"sayampaṭibhānan’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has no superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision "
"worthy of the noble ones …’ "

msgctxt "mn12:34.3"
msgid ""
"taṃ, sāriputta, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ "
"appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""
"Unless they give up that speech and that thought, and let go of that view, "
"they will be cast down to hell."

msgctxt "mn12:34.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya, evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, sāriputta, vadāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:34.5"
msgid ""
"Taṃ vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā "
"yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya35"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.74"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc34"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:35.1"
msgid "Pañca kho imā, sāriputta, gatiyo."
msgstr "There are these five destinations."

msgctxt "mn12:35.2"
msgid "Katamā pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "mn12:35.3"
msgid "Nirayo, tiracchānayoni, pettivisayo, manussā, devā."
msgstr "Hell, the animal realm, the ghost realm, humanity, and the gods."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya36"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:36.1"
msgid ""
"Nirayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nirayagāmiñca maggaṃ, nirayagāminiñca "
"paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr "I understand hell, and the path and practice that leads to hell."

msgctxt "mn12:36.2"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, "
"after death, is reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell."

msgctxt "mn12:36.3"
msgid ""
"Tiracchānayoniñcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, tiracchānayonigāmiñca maggaṃ, "
"tiracchānayonigāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr "I understand the animal realm …"

msgctxt "mn12:36.4"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjati "
"tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:36.5"
msgid ""
"Pettivisayañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, pettivisayagāmiñca maggaṃ, "
"pettivisayagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:36.6"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjati tañca "
"pajānāmi."
msgstr "the ghost realm …"

msgctxt "mn12:36.7"
msgid ""
"Manusse cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, manussalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, "
"manussalokagāminiñca paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr "humanity …"

msgctxt "mn12:36.8"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjati tañca "
"pajānāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:36.9"
msgid ""
"Deve cāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, devalokagāmiñca maggaṃ, devalokagāminiñca "
"paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr "gods, and the path and practice that leads to the world of the gods."

msgctxt "mn12:36.10"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapajjati tañca pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I understand how someone practicing that way, when their body breaks up, "
"after death, is reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "mn12:36.11"
msgid ""
"Nibbānañcāhaṃ, sāriputta, pajānāmi, nibbānagāmiñca maggaṃ, nibbānagāminiñca "
"paṭipadaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"And I understand extinguishment, and the path and practice that leads to "
"extinguishment."

msgctxt "mn12:36.12"
msgid ""
"yathā paṭipanno ca āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati tañca "
"pajānāmi."
msgstr ""
"And I understand how someone practicing that way realizes the undefiled "
"freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and lives having "
"realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya37"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc35"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:37.1"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:37.2"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"when their body breaks up, after death, they will be reborn in a place of "
"loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.’"

msgctxt "mn12:37.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in hell, where "
"they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe."

msgctxt "mn12:37.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, aṅgārakāsu sādhikaporisā pūrā aṅgārānaṃ vītaccikānaṃ "
"vītadhūmānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a pit of glowing coals deeper than a man’s height, full of "
"glowing coals that neither flamed nor smoked."

msgctxt "mn12:37.5"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva aṅgārakāsuṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same pit of coals."

msgctxt "mn12:37.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:37.7"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, "
"yathā imaṃyeva aṅgārakāsuṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very pit of coals.’"

msgctxt "mn12:37.8"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tassā aṅgārakāsuyā patitaṃ, ekantadukkhā "
"tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they see that they have indeed fallen into that pit of "
"coals, where they experience exclusively painful feelings, sharp and severe. "
"…"

msgctxt "mn12:37.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:37.10"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:37.11"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ "
"nirayaṃ upapannaṃ, ekantadukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya38"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.75"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc36"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:38.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:38.2"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr "‘This person … will be reborn in the animal realm.’"

# BB has ’etremely", but text (here and PTS) omits ekanta.
msgctxt "mn12:38.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannaṃ, "
"dukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in the animal "
"realm, where they experience painful feelings, sharp and severe."

msgctxt "mn12:38.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, gūthakūpo sādhikaporiso, pūro gūthassa."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a sewer deeper than a man’s height, full to the brim with "
"feces."

msgctxt "mn12:38.5"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva gūthakūpaṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same sewer."

msgctxt "mn12:38.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:38.7"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho "
"yathā imaṃyeva gūthakūpaṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very sewer.’"

msgctxt "mn12:38.8"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tasmiṃ gūthakūpe patitaṃ, dukkhā tibbā "
"kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they see that they have indeed fallen into that sewer, "
"where they experience painful feelings, sharp and severe. …"

msgctxt "mn12:38.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:38.10"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:38.11"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā tiracchānayoniṃ upapannaṃ, "
"dukkhā tibbā kaṭukā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc37"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:39.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:39.2"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr "‘This person … will be reborn in the ghost realm.’"

msgctxt "mn12:39.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannaṃ, "
"dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in the ghost "
"realm, where they experience many painful feelings."

msgctxt "mn12:39.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, rukkho visame bhūmibhāge jāto tanupattapalāso "
"kabaracchāyo."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a tree growing on rugged ground, with thin foliage casting "
"dappled shade."

msgctxt "mn12:39.5"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva rukkhaṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same tree."

msgctxt "mn12:39.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:39.7"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, "
"yathā imaṃyeva rukkhaṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very tree.’"

# Judging from this metaphor, did the Buddha visit Australia?
msgctxt "mn12:39.8"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya, aparena samayena tassa rukkhassa chāyāya nisinnaṃ vā "
"nipannaṃ vā dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they see them sitting or lying under that tree, where "
"they experience many painful feelings. …"

msgctxt "mn12:39.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:39.10"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:39.11"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā pettivisayaṃ upapannaṃ, "
"dukkhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc38"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:40.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:40.2"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjissatīti."
msgstr "‘This person … will be reborn among human beings.’"

msgctxt "mn12:40.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannaṃ, "
"sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn among human "
"beings, where they experience many pleasant feelings."

#. VAR: sandacchāyo → saṇḍacchāyo (s1-3) | santacchāyo (mr)
msgctxt "mn12:40.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, rukkho same bhūmibhāge jāto bahalapattapalāso "
"sandacchāyo."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a tree growing on smooth ground, with abundant foliage "
"casting dense shade."

msgctxt "mn12:40.5"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva rukkhaṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same tree."

msgctxt "mn12:40.6"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:40.7"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, "
"yathā imameva rukkhaṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very tree.’"

msgctxt "mn12:40.8"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tassa rukkhassa chāyāya nisinnaṃ vā "
"nipannaṃ vā sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they see them sitting or lying under that tree, where "
"they experience many pleasant feelings. …"

msgctxt "mn12:40.9"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:40.10"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:40.11"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā manussesu upapannaṃ, "
"sukhabahulā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya41"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.76"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc39"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:41.1"
msgid ""
"Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:41.2"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissatī’ti."
msgstr "‘This person … will be reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.’"

msgctxt "mn12:41.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapannaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed been reborn in a heavenly "
"realm, where they experience exclusively pleasant feelings."

msgctxt "mn12:41.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, pāsādo, tatrāssa kūṭāgāraṃ ullittāvalittaṃ nivātaṃ "
"phusitaggaḷaṃ pihitavātapānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a stilt longhouse with a peaked roof, plastered inside and "
"out, draft-free, with latches fastened and windows shuttered."

msgctxt "mn12:41.5"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssa pallaṅko gonakatthato paṭikatthato paṭalikatthato "
"kadalimigapavarapaccattharaṇo sauttaracchado ubhatolohitakūpadhāno."
msgstr ""
"And it had a couch spread with woolen covers—shag-piled, pure white, or "
"embroidered with flowers—and spread with a fine deer hide, with a canopy "
"above and red pillows at both ends."

msgctxt "mn12:41.6"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva pāsādaṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same stilt longhouse."

msgctxt "mn12:41.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:41.8"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, "
"yathā imaṃyeva pāsādaṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very stilt longhouse.’"

msgctxt "mn12:41.9"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena tasmiṃ pāsāde tasmiṃ kūṭāgāre tasmiṃ "
"pallaṅke nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they see them sitting or lying in that stilt longhouse, "
"where they experience exclusively pleasant feelings. …"

msgctxt "mn12:41.10"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi—"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:41.11"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho yathā "
"kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjissatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:41.12"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ "
"upapannaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ. (5)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya42"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.77"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc40"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:42.1"
msgid "Idha panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaccaṃ puggalaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi—"
msgstr "When I’ve comprehended the mind of a certain person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:42.2"
msgid ""
"tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatīti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements.’"

msgctxt "mn12:42.3"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharantaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed realized the undefiled "
"freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having "
"realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements, "
"experiencing exclusively pleasant feelings."

msgctxt "mn12:42.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, pokkharaṇī acchodakā sātodakā sītodakā setakā "
"supatitthā ramaṇīyā."
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a lotus pond with clear, sweet, cool water, clean, with "
"smooth banks, delightful."

msgctxt "mn12:42.5"
msgid "Avidūre cassā tibbo vanasaṇḍo."
msgstr "And nearby was a dark forest grove."

msgctxt "mn12:42.6"
msgid ""
"Atha puriso āgaccheyya ghammābhitatto ghammapareto kilanto tasito pipāsito "
"ekāyanena maggena tameva pokkharaṇiṃ paṇidhāya."
msgstr ""
"Then along comes a person struggling in the oppressive heat, weary, thirsty, "
"and parched. But the path they’re on heads in one direction only, to that "
"very same lotus pond."

msgctxt "mn12:42.7"
msgid "Tamenaṃ cakkhumā puriso disvā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "If a person with good eyesight saw them, they’d say:"

msgctxt "mn12:42.8"
msgid ""
"‘tathā bhavaṃ puriso paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, "
"yathā imaṃyeva pokkharaṇiṃ āgamissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is proceeding in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will arrive at that very lotus pond.’"

msgctxt "mn12:42.9"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passeyya aparena samayena taṃ pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā nhāyitvā ca "
"pivitvā ca sabbadarathakilamathapariḷāhaṃ paṭippassambhetvā paccuttaritvā "
"tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe nisinnaṃ vā nipannaṃ vā, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later they would see that person after they had plunged into "
"that lotus pond, bathed and drunk. When all their stress, weariness, and "
"heat exhaustion had faded away, they emerged and sat or lay down in that "
"woodland thicket, where they experienced exclusively pleasant feelings."

msgctxt "mn12:42.10"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, idhekaccaṃ puggalaṃ evaṃ cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, when I’ve comprehended the mind of a person, I understand:"

msgctxt "mn12:42.11"
msgid ""
"‘tathāyaṃ puggalo paṭipanno tathā ca iriyati tañca maggaṃ samārūḷho, yathā "
"āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ "
"abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This person is practicing in such a way and has entered such a path that "
"they will realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in "
"this very life, and live having realized it with their own insight due to "
"the ending of defilements.’"

msgctxt "mn12:42.12"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ passāmi aparena samayena āsavānaṃ khayā anāsavaṃ cetovimuttiṃ "
"paññāvimuttiṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja "
"viharantaṃ, ekantasukhā vedanā vedayamānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then some time later I see that they have indeed realized the undefiled "
"freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life, and live having "
"realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements, "
"experiencing exclusively pleasant feelings."

msgctxt "mn12:42.13"
msgid "Imā kho, sāriputta, pañca gatiyo."
msgstr "These are the five destinations."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya43"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc41"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:43.1"
msgid "Yo kho maṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ jānantaṃ evaṃ passantaṃ evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "When I know and see in this way, suppose someone were to say this:"

msgctxt "mn12:43.2"
msgid ""
"‘natthi samaṇassa gotamassa uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso;"
msgstr ""
"‘The ascetic Gotama has no superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision "
"worthy of the noble ones."

msgctxt "mn12:43.3"
msgid ""
"takkapariyāhataṃ samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ deseti vīmaṃsānucaritaṃ "
"sayampaṭibhānan’ti "
msgstr ""
"He teaches what he’s worked out by logic, following a line of inquiry, "
"expressing his own perspective.’ "

msgctxt "mn12:43.4"
msgid ""
"taṃ, sāriputta, vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ "
"appaṭinissajjitvā yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""
"Unless they give up that speech and that thought, and let go of that view, "
"they will be cast down to hell."

msgctxt "mn12:43.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, bhikkhu sīlasampanno samādhisampanno paññāsampanno "
"diṭṭheva dhamme aññaṃ ārādheyya; evaṃ sampadamidaṃ, sāriputta, vadāmi"
msgstr ""
"Just as a mendicant accomplished in ethics, immersion, and wisdom would "
"reach enlightenment in this very life, such is the consequence, I say."

msgctxt "mn12:43.6"
msgid ""
"taṃ vācaṃ appahāya taṃ cittaṃ appahāya taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissajjitvā "
"yathābhataṃ nikkhitto evaṃ niraye."
msgstr ""
"Unless they give up that speech and thought, and let go of that view, they "
"will be cast down to hell."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya44"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.78"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc42"></a>
#. VAR: caritā → caritvā (mr)
msgctxt "mn12:44.1"
msgid ""
"Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, caturaṅgasamannāgataṃ brahmacariyaṃ "
"caritā—"
msgstr ""
"Sāriputta, I recall having practiced a spiritual path consisting of four "
"factors."

#. VAR: pavivitto sudaṃ → ­pavi­vittas­sudaṃ (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: lūkho sudaṃ → lūkhassudaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn12:44.2"
msgid ""
"tapassī sudaṃ homi paramatapassī, lūkho sudaṃ homi paramalūkho, jegucchī "
"sudaṃ homi paramajegucchī, pavivitto sudaṃ homi paramapavivitto."
msgstr ""
"I used to be a self-mortifier, the ultimate self-mortifier. I used to live "
"rough, the ultimate rough-liver. I used to be a shunner, the ultimate "
"shunner. I used to be secluded, in ultimate seclusion."

#. <a class="nya" id="nya45"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:45.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, tapassitāya hoti—acelako homi muttācāro "
"hatthāpalekhano, naehibhaddantiko natiṭṭhabhaddantiko; nābhihaṭaṃ na "
"uddissakataṃ na nimantanaṃ sādiyāmi."
msgstr ""
"And this is what my self-mortification was like. I went naked, ignoring "
"conventions. I licked my hands, and didn’t come or stop when asked. I didn’t "
"consent to food brought to me, or food prepared specially for me, or an "
"invitation for a meal."

#. VAR: pāyamānāya → pāyantiyā (mr)
msgctxt "mn12:45.2"
msgid ""
"So na kumbhimukhā paṭiggaṇhāmi, na kaḷopimukhā paṭiggaṇhāmi, na "
"eḷakamantaraṃ, na daṇḍamantaraṃ, na musalamantaraṃ, na dvinnaṃ "
"bhuñjamānānaṃ, na gabbhiniyā, na pāyamānāya, na purisantaragatāya, na "
"saṅkittīsu, na yattha sā upaṭṭhito hoti, na yattha makkhikā saṇḍasaṇḍacārinī;"
" na macchaṃ na maṃsaṃ na suraṃ na merayaṃ na thusodakaṃ pivāmi;"
msgstr ""
"I didn’t receive anything from a pot or bowl; or from someone who keeps "
"sheep, or who has a weapon or a shovel in their home; or where a couple is "
"eating; or where there is a woman who is pregnant, breastfeeding, or who has "
"a man in her home; or where food for distribution is advertised; or where "
"there’s a dog waiting or flies buzzing. I accepted no fish or meat or liquor "
"or wine, and drank no beer."

msgctxt "mn12:45.3"
msgid ""
"so ekāgāriko vā homi ekālopiko, dvāgāriko vā homi dvālopiko … pe … "
"sattāgāriko vā homi sattālopiko;"
msgstr ""
"I went to just one house for alms, taking just one mouthful, or two houses "
"and two mouthfuls, up to seven houses and seven mouthfuls."

msgctxt "mn12:45.4"
msgid ""
"ekissāpi dattiyā yāpemi, dvīhipi dattīhi yāpemi … pe … sattahipi dattīhi "
"yāpemi;"
msgstr ""
"I fed on one saucer a day, two saucers a day, up to seven saucers a day."

msgctxt "mn12:45.5"
msgid ""
"ekāhikampi āhāraṃ āhāremi, dvīhikampi āhāraṃ āhāremi … pe … sattāhikampi "
"āhāraṃ āhāremi; iti evarūpaṃ addhamāsikampi "
"pariyāyabhattabhojanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"I ate once a day, once every second day, up to once a week, and so on, even "
"up to once a fortnight. I lived committed to the practice of eating food at "
"set intervals."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc43"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:45.6"
msgid ""
"So sākabhakkho vā homi, sāmākabhakkho vā homi, nīvārabhakkho vā homi, "
"daddulabhakkho vā homi, haṭabhakkho vā homi, kaṇabhakkho vā homi, "
"ācāmabhakkho vā homi, piññākabhakkho vā homi, tiṇabhakkho vā homi, "
"gomayabhakkho vā homi, vanamūlaphalāhāro yāpemi pavattaphalabhojī."
msgstr ""
"I ate herbs, millet, wild rice, poor rice, water lettuce, rice bran, scum "
"from boiling rice, sesame flour, grass, or cow dung. I survived on forest "
"roots and fruits, or eating fallen fruit."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc44"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:45.7"
msgid ""
"So sāṇānipi dhāremi, masāṇānipi dhāremi, chavadussānipi dhāremi, "
"paṃsukūlānipi dhāremi, tirīṭānipi dhāremi, ajinampi dhāremi, ajinakkhipampi "
"dhāremi, kusacīrampi dhāremi, vākacīrampi dhāremi, phalakacīrampi dhāremi, "
"kesakambalampi dhāremi, vāḷakambalampi dhāremi, ulūkapakkhampi dhāremi;"
msgstr ""
"I wore robes of sunn hemp, mixed hemp, corpse-wrapping cloth, rags, lodh "
"tree bark, antelope hide (whole or in strips), kusa grass, bark, wood-chips, "
"human hair, horse-tail hair, or owls’ wings."

msgctxt "mn12:45.8"
msgid "kesamassulocakopi homi kesamassulocanānuyogamanuyutto;"
msgstr "I tore out hair and beard, committed to this practice."

msgctxt "mn12:45.9"
msgid "ubbhaṭṭhakopi homi āsanapaṭikkhitto;"
msgstr "I constantly stood, refusing seats."

msgctxt "mn12:45.10"
msgid "ukkuṭikopi homi ukkuṭikappadhānamanuyutto;"
msgstr "I squatted, committed to the endeavor of squatting."

msgctxt "mn12:45.11"
msgid "kaṇṭakāpassayikopi homi kaṇṭakāpassaye seyyaṃ kappemi;"
msgstr "I lay on a mat of thorns, making a mat of thorns my bed."

msgctxt "mn12:45.12"
msgid "sāyatatiyakampi udakorohanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi—"
msgstr ""
"I was committed to the practice of immersion in water three times a day, "
"including the evening."

msgctxt "mn12:45.13"
msgid ""
"iti evarūpaṃ anekavihitaṃ kāyassa ātāpanaparitāpanānuyogamanuyutto viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"And so I lived committed to practicing these various ways of mortifying and "
"tormenting the body."

msgctxt "mn12:45.14"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, tapassitāya hoti."
msgstr "Such was my practice of self-mortification."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya46"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc45"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:46.1"
msgid "Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, lūkhasmiṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And this is what my rough living was like."

msgctxt "mn12:46.2"
msgid "nekavassagaṇikaṃ rajojallaṃ kāye sannicitaṃ hoti papaṭikajātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"The dust and dirt built up on my body over many years until it started "
"flaking off."

msgctxt "mn12:46.3"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, tindukakhāṇu nekavassagaṇiko sannicito hoti "
"papaṭikajāto, evamevāssu me, sāriputta, nekavassagaṇikaṃ rajojallaṃ kāye "
"sannicitaṃ hoti papaṭikajātaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s like the trunk of a pale-moon ebony tree, which builds up bark over "
"many years until it starts flaking off."

msgctxt "mn12:46.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, na evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "But it didn’t occur to me:"

msgctxt "mn12:46.5"
msgid ""
"‘aho vatāhaṃ imaṃ rajojallaṃ pāṇinā parimajjeyyaṃ, aññe vā pana me imaṃ "
"rajojallaṃ pāṇinā parimajjeyyun’ti."
msgstr "‘Oh, this dust and dirt must be rubbed off by my hand or another’s.’"

msgctxt "mn12:46.6"
msgid "Evampi me, sāriputta, na hoti."
msgstr "That didn’t occur to me."

msgctxt "mn12:46.7"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, lūkhasmiṃ hoti. (1)"
msgstr "Such was my rough living."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya47"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc46"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:47.1"
msgid "Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, jegucchismiṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And this is what my practice of shunning was like."

msgctxt "mn12:47.2"
msgid ""
"so kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, satova abhikkamāmi, satova paṭikkamāmi, yāva "
"udakabindumhipi me dayā paccupaṭṭhitā hoti:"
msgstr ""
"I’d step forward or back ever so mindfully. I was full of pity even "
"regarding a drop of water, thinking:"

# I’m not sure that BB’s “in the crevices” here makes sense. If they’re inn a crevice, would you just step over them? At AN 10.21 the identical phrase in a different context is rendered, “let me not harm small creatures that cross my path”. It’s interesting that the thoughts of the ascetic and the lion are the same.
msgctxt "mn12:47.3"
msgid "‘māhaṃ khuddake pāṇe visamagate saṅghātaṃ āpādesin’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘May I not accidentally injure any little creatures that happen to be in the "
"wrong place.’"

msgctxt "mn12:47.4"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, jegucchismiṃ hoti. (2)"
msgstr "Such was my practice of shunning."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya48"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.79"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc47"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:48.1"
msgid "Tatrāssu me idaṃ, sāriputta, pavivittasmiṃ hoti—"
msgstr "And this is what my seclusion was like."

msgctxt "mn12:48.2"
msgid "so kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, aññataraṃ araññāyatanaṃ ajjhogāhetvā viharāmi."
msgstr "I would plunge deep into a wilderness region and stay there."

#. VAR: sampatāmi → papatāmi (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn12:48.3"
msgid ""
"Yadā passāmi gopālakaṃ vā pasupālakaṃ vā tiṇahārakaṃ vā kaṭṭhahārakaṃ vā "
"vanakammikaṃ vā, vanena vanaṃ gahanena gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ "
"sampatāmi."
msgstr ""
"When I saw a cowherd or a shepherd, or someone gathering grass or sticks, or "
"a lumberjack, I’d flee from forest to forest, from thicket to thicket, from "
"valley to valley, from uplands to uplands."

msgctxt "mn12:48.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "mn12:48.5"
msgid "Mā maṃ te addasaṃsu ahañca mā te addasanti."
msgstr "So that I wouldn’t see them, nor they me."

msgctxt "mn12:48.6"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, sāriputta, āraññako mago manusse disvā vanena vanaṃ gahanena "
"gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ sampatati;"
msgstr "I fled like a wild deer seeing a human being."

msgctxt "mn12:48.7"
msgid ""
"evameva kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, yadā passāmi gopālakaṃ vā pasupālakaṃ vā "
"tiṇahārakaṃ vā kaṭṭhahārakaṃ vā vanakammikaṃ vā vanena vanaṃ gahanena "
"gahanaṃ ninnena ninnaṃ thalena thalaṃ sampatāmi."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:48.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:48.9"
msgid "Mā maṃ te addasaṃsu ahañca mā te addasanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn12:48.10"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, pavivittasmiṃ hoti. (3)"
msgstr "Such was my practice of seclusion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya49"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc48"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:49.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ye te goṭṭhā paṭṭhitagāvo apagatagopālakā, tattha "
"catukkuṇḍiko upasaṅkamitvā yāni tāni vacchakānaṃ taruṇakānaṃ dhenupakānaṃ "
"gomayāni tāni sudaṃ āhāremi."
msgstr ""
"I would go on all fours into the cow-pens after the cattle had left and eat "
"the dung of the young suckling calves."

msgctxt "mn12:49.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvakīvañca me, sāriputta, sakaṃ muttakarīsaṃ apariyādinnaṃ hoti, sakaṃyeva "
"sudaṃ muttakarīsaṃ āhāremi."
msgstr "As long as my own urine and excrement lasted, I would even eat that."

# Mahavikata is a Vinaya term for these things when eaten, i.e. the phrase doesn’t mean “distortion in eating “but” eating of distorted things”.
msgctxt "mn12:49.3"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, mahāvikaṭabhojanasmiṃ hoti. (4)"
msgstr "Such was my eating of most unnatural things."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya50"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc49"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:50.1"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, aññataraṃ bhiṃsanakaṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ ajjhogāhetvā "
"viharāmi."
msgstr "I would plunge deep into an awe-inspiring forest grove and stay there."

msgctxt "mn12:50.2"
msgid ""
"Tatrāssudaṃ, sāriputta, bhiṃsanakassa vanasaṇḍassa bhiṃsanakatasmiṃ hoti—"
msgstr "It was so awe-inspiring that"

msgctxt "mn12:50.3"
msgid "yo koci avītarāgo taṃ vanasaṇḍaṃ pavisati, yebhuyyena lomāni haṃsanti."
msgstr ""
"normally it would make your hair stand on end if you weren’t free of greed."

#. VAR: antaraṭṭhakā himapātasamayā → antaraṭṭhake himapātasamaye (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn12:50.4"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, yā tā rattiyo sītā hemantikā antaraṭṭhakā "
"himapātasamayā tathārūpāsu rattīsu rattiṃ abbhokāse viharāmi, divā vanasaṇḍe;"
msgstr ""
"And on cold nights like the eight days of winter when the snow falls I "
"stayed in the open by night and in the forest by day."

msgctxt "mn12:50.5"
msgid "gimhānaṃ pacchime māse divā abbhokāse viharāmi, rattiṃ vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"But in the last month of summer I’d stay in the open by day and in the "
"forest by night."

msgctxt "mn12:50.6"
msgid ""
"Apissu maṃ, sāriputta, ayaṃ anacchariyagāthā paṭibhāsi pubbe assutapubbā:"
msgstr ""
"And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor "
"learned before in the past, occurred to me:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc50"></a>
#. VAR: sosinno → sosīno (bj, s1, s2, pts1, mr) | so sino (s3) | sosindo (saddanīti)
msgctxt "mn12:50.7"
msgid "‘Sotatto sosinno ceva,"
msgstr "‘Scorched and frozen,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn12:50.8"
msgid "eko bhiṃsanake vane;"
msgstr "alone in the awe-inspiring forest."

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn12:50.9"
msgid "Naggo na caggimāsīno,"
msgstr "Naked, no fire to sit beside,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn12:50.10"
msgid "esanāpasuto munī’ti."
msgstr "the sage still pursues his quest.’"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya51"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc51"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:51.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, susāne seyyaṃ kappemi chavaṭṭhikāni upadhāya."
msgstr ""
"I would make my bed in a charnel ground, with the bones of the dead for a "
"pillow."

#. VAR: gāmaṇḍalā → gomaṇḍalā (bahūsu)
msgctxt "mn12:51.2"
msgid ""
"Apissu maṃ, sāriputta, gāmaṇḍalā upasaṅkamitvā oṭṭhubhantipi, omuttentipi, "
"paṃsukenapi okiranti, kaṇṇasotesupi salākaṃ pavesenti."
msgstr ""
"Then the cowboys would come up to me. They’d spit and piss on me, throw mud "
"on me, even poke sticks in my ears."

msgctxt "mn12:51.3"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, abhijānāmi tesu pāpakaṃ cittaṃ uppādetā."
msgstr "But I don’t recall ever having a bad thought about them."

msgctxt "mn12:51.4"
msgid "Idaṃsu me, sāriputta, upekkhāvihārasmiṃ hoti."
msgstr "Such was my abiding in equanimity."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya52"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.80"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc52"></a>
msgctxt "mn12:52.1"
msgid "Santi kho pana, sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā evaṃvādino evaṃdiṭṭhino:"
msgstr "There are some ascetics and brahmins who have this doctrine and view:"

msgctxt "mn12:52.2"
msgid "‘āhārena suddhī’ti."
msgstr "‘Purity comes from food.’"

msgctxt "mn12:52.3"
msgid "Te evamāhaṃsu:"
msgstr "They say:"

msgctxt "mn12:52.4"
msgid "‘kolehi yāpemā’ti."
msgstr "‘Let’s live on jujubes.’"

msgctxt "mn12:52.5"
msgid "Te kolampi khādanti, kolacuṇṇampi khādanti, kolodakampi pivanti—"
msgstr "So they eat jujubes and jujube powder, and drink jujube juice."

# BB’s “make” is incorrect, there is no insinuation that they made these themselves.
msgctxt "mn12:52.6"
msgid "anekavihitampi kolavikatiṃ paribhuñjanti."
msgstr "And they enjoy many jujube concoctions."

# I’m not convinced by BB’s “per day” here, there is no āha.
msgctxt "mn12:52.7"
msgid "Abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva kolaṃ āhāraṃ āhāritā."
msgstr "I recall eating just a single jujube."

msgctxt "mn12:52.8"
msgid "Siyā kho pana te, sāriputta, evamassa:"
msgstr "You might think that"

msgctxt "mn12:52.9"
msgid "‘mahā nūna tena samayena kolo ahosī’ti."
msgstr "at that time the jujubes must have been very big."

msgctxt "mn12:52.10"
msgid "Na kho panetaṃ, sāriputta, evaṃ daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr "But you should not see it like this."

msgctxt "mn12:52.11"
msgid "Tadāpi etaparamoyeva kolo ahosi seyyathāpi etarahi."
msgstr "The jujubes then were at most the same size as today."

msgctxt "mn12:52.12"
msgid ""
"Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, ekaṃyeva kolaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato adhimattakasimānaṃ "
"patto kāyo hoti."
msgstr "Eating so very little, my body became extremely emaciated."

msgctxt "mn12:52.13"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me "
"aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty year "
"old or a corpse,"

msgctxt "mn12:52.14"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "my bottom became like a camel’s hoof,"

msgctxt "mn12:52.15"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako unnatāvanato hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string,"

msgctxt "mn12:52.16"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me "
"phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr "and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn."

msgctxt "mn12:52.17"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti;"
" evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, "
"like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well."

#. VAR: samphuṭito → saṃphusito (s1-3) | sampuṭito (pts1) | saṃpuṭito (mr)
msgctxt "mn12:52.18"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti "
"sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-"
"gourd in the wind and sun."

msgctxt "mn12:52.19"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva "
"pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva "
"pariggaṇhāmi, yāvassu me, sāriputta, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti "
"tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that "
"when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I "
"tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly."

msgctxt "mn12:52.20"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo "
"papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face "
"down right there."

msgctxt "mn12:52.21"
msgid ""
"So kho ahaṃ, sāriputta, tameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anomajjāmi. "
"Tassa mayhaṃ, sāriputta, pāṇinā gattāni anomajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā "
"patanti tāyevappāhāratāya."
msgstr ""
"Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs "
"with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out."

